short-description: The Turner Motorsport E46 M54 Silicone Intake boot is designed with a smooth contour for improved air flow compared to the OE corrugated rubber, featuring Stepped flanges to maintain smooth ID transition from air box to throttle body. Silicone also offers reduced thermal conductivity as well as improved resistance to ozone and UV degradation for improved performance and durability.

cleanDesc: Turner Motorsport N54 Silicone Turbo Inlet Hose Kit - Stock Location...
short-description: If you have owned your BMW for any length of time, you are most likely aware of BMW's less-than-stellar reputation for developing weak plastic hoses and other parts. A great example of this are the N54 turbo inlet pipes. Over time, constant temperature swings cause these plastic pipes/hoses to become brittle. This often leads to cracks, splits, or even complete failure, allowing your turbos to suck in unfiltered air. To prevent this from happening to you, we are proud to present our very own Turner Motorsport N54 Silicone Turbo Inlet Hoses! Silicone inlet hoses are extremely reliable, resisting heat and pressure significantly better than plastic. This is perfect people who are just looking for a simple, reliable upgrade, or people who want to push the limits of their BMW and are looking to make more boost and more power without worrying about failing inlets. Available in two sizes, our kits can support either stock (44mm) or upgraded (50mm) turbos and include adapters to reconnect your turbo bypass pipes. If you plan to upgrade your charge pipes, replace the stock diverter valves with aftermarket atmospheric blow-off-valves, or want to convert your BMW to a catch can system, we also recommend the optionally available Turner Motorsport N54 Inlet Hose Plug Kit. This kit blocks off the turbo bypass pipe connections and PCV connections that will no longer be needed.

These two "scoops" install behind your front grills to direct more airflow into the factory intake snorkel used on the 2008, 2009 (and newer) E82 and E88 1 series BMWs, including 128i and 135i. Scoops are a direct bolt-in install, and include installation instructions and required hardware for a simple install. short-description: If you've already replaced the factory airbox of your E46 M3 for a cold air intake kit, the stock rubber intake elbow (which connects the mass air sensor / HFM to the intake manifold) is now your enemy. The stock S54 part has accordian-like grooves on both the inlet and outlet side, which slows down air flow. It's no wonder you don't see this type of restrictive setup on the E46 M3 CSL!    The Samco silicone intake boot for E46 M3 has a perfectly smooth interior surface, engineered for the best flow and smoothest transision -- no sharp edges or angles to hang up or slow down the air. Made in the UK using a 4 layer silicone design. Unlike the stock E46 M3 rubber boot, which is prone to drying, cracking and leaking, the Samco boot is virtually indestructable and ready for the rigors of heat temperature and extreme conditions.      2001-2006    coupe & convertible

ARM Relocated Silicone Inlet Intake Kit - N54 - 1.75" Turbo Inl...
short-description: The ARM Motorsports N54 Inlets are the ultimate relocated inlet system for your N54. Relocating the inlets on your N54 with the ARM Inlets increase the power and torque of your N54 up to 60whp/60wtq. Expect improved turbo spool, faster peak boost, and more volume from the turbochargers on your N54. If you're looking to max out your stock or upgraded twin turbochargers these are a must! Highlights: Gains of up to 60whp/60wtq Quicker Turbo Spool Increased Turbo Volume One of the greatest challenges when upgrading to relocated inlets on your N54 is mitigating the heat of the air induced by the turbos. With the inlets relocated to the passenger-side the filters are closer to the turbochargers where temperatures are hotter. The ARM N54 Inlets come with a manifold heat shield which serves to help keep heat down near the turbos and away from the inlet filters. This also assists with keeping heat away from the inlet tubes themselves. In addition, the ARM Inlets come with an air filter heat shield which assists in keeping the cooler air near the filters separate from hotter air coming from the engine adjacent to it. The air filters on the ARM Inlets are secured in place with a filter bracket which prevents filters and inlets themselves from bouncing around during acceleration, braking, and cornering. Also included with the ARM Inlets is a support bracket for the boost solenoids. This keeps them locked into place during extreme driving. To help make installation easy, relocation brackets for the coolant reservoir and power steering pump reservoir are included with the ARM Inlets. Kit Includes: ARM Relocated Inlets Manifold Heat Shield Air Filter Head Shield Coolant Reservoir Relocation Brackets Power Steering Reservoir Relocation Bracket Boost Solenoid Bracket Clamps

short-description: If you are about to (or already have) eliminated the restrictive stock BMW ASC+T traction control system, you'll want to upgrade to this Samco silicone intake boot. Lose the factory "accordian" desgin boot, which creates lots of intake turbulence (read: lost power!). The Samco intake elbow has a perfectly smooth interior finish, with no sharp angles or other obstacles for intake air to get slowed by. It's made using 4 layers of high quality silicone, designed to last for many years in even the most extreme conditions.     (You'll also need to install a 10ohm / 1watt resistor accross the ASC actuator wiring, to simulate the presence of the ASC modules, and avoid causing ABS faults). Removing ASC is a great way to decrease intake restriction, and this intake boot is perfect for this upgrade. We offer an   if you are deleting ACS.    This intake boot works very well with all cold air intake kits, including the Conforti cold air kit (with standard 3.0" HFM) and AFE intake kits.    No problem! We have a Samco intake bellows for that application as well (see part# SAMCO-BFHOSE1-BLK).      1992-1995    325i, 325is & 325ic  1996-1999    328i, 328is & 328ic (with ASC delete)  1995-1999    3.0 & 3.2 (with ASC delete)  1997-1999    2.3 & 2.8 liter  1998-2000    (S52 engine)

cleanDesc: Samco Silicone Intake Boot - Black - E46 M3
short-description: If you've already replaced the factory airbox of your E46 M3 for a cold air intake kit, the stock rubber intake elbow (which connects the mass air sensor / HFM to the intake manifold) is now your enemy. The stock S54 part has accordian-like grooves on both the inlet and outlet side, which slows down air flow. It's no wonder you don't see this type of restrictive setup on the E46 M3 CSL!    The Samco silicone intake boot for E46 M3 has a perfectly smooth interior surface, engineered for the best flow and smoothest transision -- no sharp edges or angles to hang up or slow down the air. Made in the UK using a 4 layer silicone design. Unlike the stock E46 M3 rubber boot, which is prone to drying, cracking and leaking, the Samco boot is virtually indestructable and ready for the rigors of heat temperature and extreme conditions.      2001-2006    coupe & convertible

short-description: This intake book fits BMW E30 M3 from 1988-1991. This boot goes from the air flow meter to the air accumulator. A cracked intake boot can cause problems with erratic idle, poor fuel economy and potentially damage the engine by letting debris directly into the engine. We recommend checking the intake boots at least once a year.      1988-1991   M3
